16. WP Staging Issue — Current State
At end of session the Chrome extension was performing a reclone of production back to staging and got hung. Extension froze with error: messages.19.content.27.image.source.base64.data: At least one of the image dimensions exceed max allowed size for many-image requests: 2000 pixels

Recovery: Close hung extension session. Check WP Staging in WordPress dashboard to see if clone completed or errored. Start fresh extension session if needed.

Prevention: Tell extension at session start: "Do not take screenshots. Describe what you see in text only."


17. Workflow Notes
Preferred workflow:

Design decisions → Claude chat (this session)
Implementation → Chrome extension (focused single-task sessions)
Review → Claude chat fetches live site, compares against spec
Reconcile → update GitHub docs via web editor

Chrome extension tips:

Start each session with a focused task, not the whole build plan
Paste only the relevant section of the spec, not all four docs
Say "Do not take screenshots" to avoid image size errors and save tokens
Say "Copy text verbatim from the source document — do not rewrite"
Claude in Chrome uses Haiku model — fast but less capable; come back to main chat for complex decisions

Token management:

Steve's weekly limit resets Monday 9am
Long single sessions are expensive — shorter focused sessions are cheaper
Moving to a Claude Project recommended for future sessions



